cket.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is shared-state coordination across concurrent callers/modules. Unit-testing a bucket class alone can miss wiring bugs (per-client bucket accidental duplication).","test_description":"Instantiate multiple callers against the same process-level client/quota manager; fire concurrent call() requests and assert consumed tokens/blocked retries reflect one shared bucket, not per-caller independent quotas.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.86,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When multiple requests are waiting to be sent, they are dispatched in the order they were originally submitted.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Ordering bugs emerge from interaction of queue, scheduler, and dispatcher under async contention. Unit tests on queue internals alone can miss dispatch-layer reordering.","test_description":"Submit several requests quickly while send path is blocked/rate-limited, then release capacity stepwise; assert transport sees dispatch sequence matching original submission order (FIFO).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
